        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 25 at 5:24PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from near Greenwich to near Mechanicville to Latham.
Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and brief, heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Troy, Cohoes, Watervliet, Hoosick Falls, Salem, Green Island,
Waterford, Cambridge, Greenwich, Center Brunswick, Hoosick, Lee,
Pittstown, White Creek, Easton, Schuylerville, Schaghticoke, Valley
Falls, Cossayuna, and Schaghticoke Hill.

This includes Interstate 787 between exits 8 and 9.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
